SPECIAL MESSAGE - SCHOOL CLOSURE
Governor Murphy has extended NJ School Closures through at least 5/15 to ensure the safety and health of everyone.
Next Remote Board Meeting, Tuesday, 4/21
Conference Call (701) 801-6381 (no access code necessary)
Meals will be available for pickup twice a week, Monday and Wednesday, 9AM - 11AM, due to the Governor’s Shelter-in-Place order.
We will distribute Monday and Tuesday meals on Monday, and Wednesday through Friday meals on Wednesday. There will be NO meal pickup on Tuesday, Thursday or Friday.
NJ Child Care Options can be viewed here.
View the Keep Americans Connected Pledge (free Internet access) here.
Dear Parents - This is a friendly reminder to regularly monitor your child’s work while schools are closed. Students must keep up with their online lessons or, in some cases, paper packets. Falling behind presents a risk of failing. Thank you for all of your support to ensure that our students continue to learn. For information on how to log on to Google Classroom, Google Hangout/Meet, or any tech site, please contact Edwin Wargo at 856-404-0462 / ewargo@compassacs.org
Compass has created a Remote Instruction Website that can be found here: 
 https://sites.google.com/compassacs.org/remoteschool/home
Stay healthy and safe!






An exceptional, free, Tier 1 
Charter School with proven results
Where all children will learn, lead, and become the future. 

 LEARN MORE 





Why Compass?


The Mission of the Compass Academy Charter School is to increase each child’s success in learning and as a result, academic achievement. Using the Let Me Learn Process® as its innovative approach, the school leadership and teachers will help students develop a stronger sense of self as learners, a greater degree of academic achievement, and a healthy lifestyle for learning. 



See for
Yourself


















Experienced Teachers
The staff at Compass are trained, certified professionals who excel in their field. Many of our educators also have supplemental training in alternative learning strategies. 










Small Class Sizes
Small class sizes means your child gets individual attention and won't be overlooked. 




















Let Me Learn
Compass uses Let Me Learn - a proven, tested way for students to identify how they best learn.





















Data & Technology
Data is used to ensure students are learning to their full potential. What's more - students track their own learning styles through Let Me Learn. Students in Grades K-5 have use Google Chromebooks. 



THE
STATS
How we compare 

 Check Out the Data 


The Department of Education ranked all schools in New Jersey on a scale of 0 to 100.
The following data was used for the ranking score:
English language arts growth (20 percent), math growth (20 percent), progress toward English language proficiency (20 percent), English language arts proficiency (15 percent), math proficiency (15 percent), chronic absenteeism (10 percent)
Compass' ranking is 61.8. 

